review_blob: On Tap.  Nice red colour, with slightly offwhite head.  A really nice DIPA that was very enjoyable to drink.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Light amber in colour, with medium creamy white head. Heavy pine and orange hop aroma. Pineapple in there somewhere. A great beer, if I was lucky enough this would be my regular IPA.

Bottle. Yellow/Amber colour, with medium frothy white head. Very feint hop aroma seeing as its all about the hops. Harsh hop aroma including lime, orange and perfume. This is a really good beer, but to be taken 1 bottle at a time!
Bottle. Amber orange in colour with a large creamy off-white head. Light malt aroma with bread and molasses. Heavy on the hops with orange and grass coming through.
On Tap @ Brewpub. Look very good in the glass, with a deep red colour and a small head. Really enjoyed drinking this beer.
beer_name: Goose Island Lake Effect Winter Ale (2002-2013)

review_blob: Bottle. Average off-white head that was quite frothy. Dark Ruby/Brown in colour. Heavy malt aroma with bread and molasses present. Minimal hops, but feint trace of perfume. Definite alcohol taste. An outstanding beer.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Dogfish Head Life & Limb

review_blob: On Tap at Brewpub. Golden colour, with minimal white head. Discreet aroma, but an easy drinking lager.
On Tap at Brewpub. Orange in colour, with a small white head. A definite malt aroma of caramel.
On tap at Brewpub. An Enjoyable IPA. Quite lively citrus hoppy aroma. A nice bitter finish means a pretty tasty beer.
On tap at brewpub. Golden colour with small diminishing head. Mild hops aroma with minimal malt undercurrent. Quite enjoyable

Enjoyed from a bottle. Lovely amber colour, with a considerable head with good lacing. Bready malts and a hint of spruce from the hops gives a well rounded experience. Easy to drink, and is a favorite session beer.
Buller Pub, Recoleta. Part of 6 beer tasting tray. Golden amber with small diminshing white head. Doesnt grab your attention with any of its characteristics.
Buller Pub, Recoleta. Part of 6 beer tasting tray. Not a great beer. Very small traces of malt and hops.
Buller Pub, Recoleta. Part of 6 beer tasting tray. Amber colour, slightly cloudy. Not particularly hoppy, but a reasonable IPA.
Buller Pub, Recoleta. Part of 6 beer tasting tray. Probably a little too sweet, even for a honey beer. Golden yellow colour, not cloudy, white head.
Buller Pub, Recoleta. Part of 6 beer tasting tray. Cloudy yellow colour, with good white head. Light hops bringing a touch of citrus.
Buller Pub, Recoleta. Part of 6 beer testing tray. Black beer with off-white head. Roasted malt, with a touch of hops.
A very light lager, that is ok on a very hot summers day, but otherwise Id pass.
A very standard lager, that is enjoyable on hot days. No stand out characteristics in any of the tasting categories.
Enjoyed this beer on during some hot days in brazil, in there cicumstances it went down a treat. However I wont be searching it out now that Im back home!
Enjoyed from a bottle. A small diminishing head, with very little lacing. Amber almost orange colour. Really nice floral/citus aroma. A pleasure to drink.
On Tap, throughout Dublin. A good pour looks delicious. Long lasting creamy off-white head, with good lacing. Feels thin in the mouth.
On tap. A very average IPA, which is a bit too fizzy! Short creamy head.
Lovely dark honey coloured appearance, with faint head. Good body and nice bitterness lead to a very pleasant beer.
beer_name: Diamond Knot Industrial India Pale Ale

review_blob: On tap, Archipelago Brewpub. A deep golden colour with quite an amount of frothy head. Enjoyable hop aroma, and mild carbonation. Good quality IPA. A good find in Singapore!

330ml Bottle served very cold. Cloudy, golden appearance. Subtle hop aroma with hint of citrus / melon. Higher than average carbonation on the palate. Enjoyable compared to other beers available locally, but below par.
